 Parliament. Unfortunately, it was not enough to defeat the attackers completely. This leads to a number of quacks who are now trying to undermine the authority of our OMT generals and slander our Prime Minister with pure personal attacks. With self-imagined truths, these charlatans undermine the science-based authority of the OMT and use it to activate demonstrations in some of the even inflammatory language, using the right of free speech. From a strategic defensive point of view, this may be a difficult side effect for the government of our rule of law, but not legally exceptional. The police's unnecessarily powerful response to the demonstrations was exceptional and led to an unnecessary rearguard fight with the demonstrators with large-scale destabilising riots. It was a culpable error of judgment on the part of the police and therefore also on the part of the government. This did not serve the fight against our real enemy, the murdering snipers. Besides, it was a waste of time. There is no point in opening a second front against quacks. They have always been there in history and history proves that in the end they shoot themselves in their own foot. The power of the scientific argument of our OMT generals is untouchable compared to the fake news of the self-appointed quasi-scientists. The people will soon recognize that and drive out the quacks in the upcoming elections with pitch and feathers. Back to the battle against the invisible army. Our defensive measures have not been sufficient so far, so our enemy has been in control of the whole country for months now. In fact, with new variants these last lines of defense are bombarded. Reason for the government to take a far-reaching defence measure against the advice of the Council of State by declaring war on the enemy in the form of the establishment of a curfew. That was a second culpable error of assessment, as this was not done on the right legal grounds. The quacks also play a dubious role in this. Instead