ops, because we too have to answer for what we are doing. Now it is being considered, in consultation with the directors of Defense, whether you can do this smarter, for example in line with what we have already done in recent years in the integration of the Rijksbouwsdienst and the Rijksbouwgoedbedrijf, that Rijksbouwingssystem. That is a system that has proven itself by now, so you could think of a modality that could also be useful for the Defense Department. Because real estate is not really the core business for Defence; that is, of course, the defence and protection of the Dutch and NATO territories. At the same time, we are now in a situation of resignation. So we will continue with the preparations, but this could be a subject that comes before the next cabinet for decision-making. I think that is a good thing, too, when we look at the critical notes that the Court of Auditors is cracking on this issue. This also applies: no one needs to be convinced that this is a problem, because it is quite clear that it is a major problem. So that has to be solved. Finally, towards Mrs Den Haan. The working relationship with Defence and the RVB is excellent, just for the sake of completeness. That brings me to the end of my reply. I would like to congratulate the three Members of Parliament who gave their maiden speech, which I enjoyed very much, and wish them every success in their duties as MPs."}, {"speech id": "ParlaMint-NL_2021-06-17-tweedekamer-16.u202", "speech text": "Yes. Then I still have the headline: outside the EU. There was a question from Mr Sjoerdsma: it is time for closer defence cooperation in the European field and the Netherlands should specialise. A great deal has already been exchanged with the Minister of Defence during the 2020 budget debate. Motions have been adopted on scenarios for possible specialisation routes within international partnerships. We're looking at how defense task specialization can take place. The Secretary of Defense is prepar